data.description: Listed on the National Historic Register this charming 1927  Craftsman home offers a blend of historic allure and modern amenities with the original wood flooring, a cozy fireplace with its custom mantle and shelves.  Updated windows, kitchen and  A/C.  Relax on the front porch and watch  Benson's annual 4th of July Parade roll by.  Across from Apache Park. Short walking distance to our award winning school district, the public library.  10 x 12 detached garage and workshop.
